headline: Tesla and 3 More Stocks Whose Charts Point to Post-Earnings Gains
summary: Moves following corporate earnings, which often clarify the technical picture for a stock, are pointing to gains for some well-known names.  The charts for  Tesla Alphabet Chipotle Mexican Grill  and  Las Vegas Sands  stand out among those for more than 100 companies, reviewed by Barron’s, that reported their earnings last week.  Shares of Tesla, which is being thought of less as an electric-vehicle play, and more of a bet on artificial intelligence, robotics and energy storage, dropped 8.1% Thursday in the stock’s first negative reaction to earnings in four quarters.
